        "title": "feat: add shared notification wake policy",
        "body": "Summary\n- Adds core `notificationWake.reactions` policy and config/schema metadata.\n- Routes Discord and Telegram reaction system events through a shared core helper, defaulting to queued-only behavior unless configured to wake or off.\n- Uses stable reaction keys for unicode/custom/paid reactions and updates docs/tests/generated metadata.\n\nVerification\n- `pnpm test src/infra/notification-system-events.test.ts src/infra/heartbeat-runner.returns-default-unset.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.test.ts src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `pnpm config:docs:check`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `codex review --uncommitted`\n- `pnpm check:changed` (Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01krxkzes07bae3pxdg46p01ax`, GitHub Actions run https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/26036167028)\n\nBehavior addressed: Discord and Telegram accepted reaction system events use core `notificationWake.reactions`; `queue` preserves queued-only behavior, `wake` requests a targeted heartbeat only after enqueue succeeds, and `off` skips enqueue.\nReal environment tested: local source checkout; Blacksmith Testbox changed gate `tbx_01krxkzes07bae3pxdg46p01ax`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: focused Vitest command above, generated metadata checks, `git diff --check`, final Codex autoreview, and Testbox `pnpm check:changed`.\nEvidence after fix: focused tests, generated config/channel/API checks, Testbox changed gate, and autoreview passed.\nObserved result after fix: reaction events queue with stable reaction keys and optional wake policy; only explicit `notification-wake:*` heartbeat requests bypass empty `HEARTBEAT.md` gating.\nWhat was not tested: live Discord/Telegram reaction event against real external accounts.\n\nRelated to #83169\nRelated to #47687\n",
